The paper focuses on image synthesis and image-to-image translation, which are tasks related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning a novel architectural unit that can be integrated into both generators and discriminators in GANs and CycleGANs, which are deep learning models for generative learning (cs.LG). The method also leverages attention mechanisms and residual connections, which are common techniques in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the Atrous spatial pyramid, which is a technique commonly used in semantic segmentation and image processing (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image datasets, which suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM).
